==English==

===Etymology===
Japanese [[漫画]] (''manga''), [[漫]] (''man-'') "random, uncontrolled" + [[画]] (''-ga'') "picture, sketch". After an 1814 book by [[w:Hokusai|Katsushika Hokusai]].

===Pronunciation===
* {{a|GenAm}} {{IPA|/ˈmæŋɡə/}}, {{SAMPA|/"m{Ng@/}}
* {{hyphenation|man|ga}}
* {{rhymes|æŋɡə}}

===Noun===
{{wikipedia}}
{{en-noun|manga}}

# {{manga}} A [[comic]]; a non-animated cartoon, especially one done in a Japanese style.
# {{manga}} A professionally produced Japanese comic, opposed to [[doujinshi]].

